ind''''' is a [[Dating show|dating]] [[reality television]] series, produced by [[ProSiebenSat.1 Media#Red Arrow Studios|Kinetic Content]]<ref name=\"new york post\">{{cite web |last1=Hegedus |first1=Eric |title=Netflix's 'Love Is Blind' confirms reality TV dating is pure trash |url=https://nypost.com/2020/01/30/netflixs-love-is-blind-confirms-reality-tv-dating-is-pure-trash/ |website=New York Post |accessdate=February 1, 2020|date=January 30, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and created by Chris Coelen<ref name=\"other engagements\">{{cite web |last1=Kinane |first1=Ruth |title=Love Is Blind creator on what they didn't show \u2014 including even more proposals |url=https://ew.com/tv/2020/02/14/love-is-blind-netflix-dating-show-creator-what-you-didnt-see/ |website=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |date=February 14, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> which premiered on [[Netflix]] on February 13, 2020 as part of a three-week event.<ref name=\"entertainment weekly\">{{cite web |last1=Snierson |first1=Dan |title=Watch singles get engaged without meeting in person in trailer for Netflix reality series |url=https://ew.com/tv/2020/01/30/love-is-blind-netflix-trailer/ |website=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=February 1, 2020|date=January 30, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>  The series has been compared to ''[[Married at First Sight (American TV series)|Married at First Sight]]'', which was also produced by Kinetic Content,<ref name=\"new york post\"/> and ''[[The Bachelor (American TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.<ref name=\"gq\">{{cite web |last1=Grebey |first1=James |title=Netflix's Love Is Blind Is the Dystopian Dating Reality Show We Deserve |url=https://www.gq.com/story/netflix-love-is-blind-dating-show |website=GQ |accessdate=February 1, 2020|date=January 30, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> A total of ten episodes were released, in addition to a reunion special that was released on Netflix and [[YouTube]] on March 5.<ref name=\"reunion\">{{cite web |last1=Heldman |first1=Breanne |title=Netflix Announces Love Is Blind Cast Reunion to Reveal Which Couples Have Stayed Together |url=https://people.com/tv/netflix-announces-love-is-blind-cast-reunion-to-reveal-which-couples-have-stayed-together/ |website=People |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 26, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Netflix]] renewed ''Love Is Blind'' for a second and third season on March 24, 2020.<ref name=\"season 2 renewal\">{{cite web |author1=Netflix |title=Moments of Joy from Real Netflix Shows - New season announcements |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u83uo2_qWo0 |website=youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |language=English |date=March 24, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"renewal\">{{cite web |last1=Thorne |first1=Will |title=Netflix Orders More 'Love Is Blind,' 'The Circle,' 'Rhythm + Flow' and Marie Kondo |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/love-is-blind-the-circle-rhythm-flow-marie-kondo-renewed-netflix-1203543386/ |website=Variety |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |language=English |date=March 24, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Format ==\nThe series follows thirty men and women hoping to find love. For ten days in a [[speed dating]] format, the men and women date each other in different \"pods\" where they can talk to each other, but not see each other. Whenever they decided, the men were able to propose to the woman they want to marry. After the proposal, and meeting face to face for the first time, the engaged couples headed to a couples retreat in [[Playa del Carmen]], [[Mexico]]. During this trip they spent time getting to know their partners, and were able to meet the other couples participating in the experiment. \n\nFollowing the couples retreat, the engaged couples moved to the same apartment complex back in Atlanta. While at the apartments, they all met their partners' families and explored their partners' living conditions. At the altar on the day of the wedding, the engaged couples carried out wedding ceremonies and needed to make their final decisions at the altar about whether to split up or get married, answering the question \"Is love blind?\"\n\n==Season summary==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|+Season 1 (February 13 \u2013 March 5, 2020) couples\n|-\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Couples\n! scope=\"col\"| Proposal\n! scope=\"col\"| Still together\n! scope=\"col\"| Relationship notes\n|-\n| Lauren Speed & Cameron Hamilton\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| The two got married in November 2018, during the filming of the 1st season of Love is Blind. The couple are still together as of {{currentmonthname}} {{currentyear}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/love-is-blind-lauren-cameron-still-together/|title=Love is Blind's Lauren Speed and Cameron Hamilton Are Still Married!|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Heldman|first=Breanne|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n| Amber Pike & Matthew Barnett\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| The two got married in November 2018, during the filming of the 1st season of Love is Blind. The couple are still together as of {{currentmonthname}} {{currentyear}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/amber-barnett-are-still-together-after-love-is-blind-theyve-been-busy-22058861|title=Love is Blind's Amber and Barnett Are Still Together!|work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]|last=Blanton|first=Kayla|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n| Gianinna Gibelli & Damian Powers\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Although the couple got engaged during the show, they spilt on their wedding day. It was revealed at the reunion special that the two were back together. The couple are still together as of {{currentmonthname}} {{currentyear}}.  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/entertainment/a31235244/love-is-blind-damian-giannina-back-together/|title=Love is Blind's Damian and Giannina Are Back Together|work=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|last=Shenton|first=Zoe|date=March 5, 2020|accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Jessica Batten & Mark Cuevas\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Although the couple got engaged during the show, they split on their wedding day.  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/film-tv/a31174427/love-is-blind-jessica-mark-relationship/|title=Are Jessica and Mark from Love is Blind Still Together?|work=[[Harper Bazaar]]|last=MacKelden|first=Amy|date=March 1, 2020|accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n| Kelly Chase & Kenny Barnes\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Although, the couple got engaged during the show, the couple split on their wedding day. At the reunion special, it was revealed that Barnes is in a relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.people.com/tv/love-is-blind-kelly-chase-kenny-barnes-rejection/|title=Love is Blind's Kelly and Kenny Never Planned On Getting Married|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Heldman|first=Breanne|date=March 5, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Diamond Jack & Carlton Morton\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Although the couple got engaged on the show, their relationship imploded after a dramatic fight during the couple's trip to [[Playa del Carmen, Mexico]] where they fought about Morton's bisexuality, the lack of communciation and Morton's derogatory comments about Jack. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a31027305/love-is-blind-diamond-carlton-now/|title=Why Love Is Blind's Carlton and Diamond Never Considered Getting Back Together|work=[[Oprah (magazine)|Oprah]]|last=Nicolaou|first=Elena|date=February 26, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Contestants ==\n<onlyinclude>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:auto;\"\n|+''Love Is Blind'' season 1 contestants\n! Name\n! Age\n! Occupation\n! Hometown\n! Relationship Status\n|-\n| Lauren Speed\n| 32\n| Content creator\n| [[Detroit, Michigan]]\n| Married, November 2018\n|-\n| Cameron Hamilton\n| 28\n| Data scientist\n| [[Lee, Maine]]\n| Married, November 2018\n|-\n| Amber Pike\n| 27\n| Ex-tank mechanic\n| [[Augusta, Georgia]]\n| Married, November 2018\n|-\n| Matthew  Barnett\n| 27\n| Engineer\n| [[Canton, Georgia]]\n| Married, November 2018 \n|-\n| Giannina Gibelli\n| 25\n| Business owner\n| [[Caracas, Venezuela]]\n| In a relationship with Damian\n|-\n| Damian Powers\n| 27\n| General manager\n| [[Heidelberg, Germany]]\n| In a relationship with Giannina\n|-\n| Jessica Batten\n| 34\n| Regional manager\n| [[Rock Falls, Illinois]]\n| Split at wedding\n|-\n| Mark Cuevas\n| 24\n| Fitness trainer\n| [[Chicago, Illinois]]\n| Split at wedding\n|-\n| Kelly Chase\n| 33\n| Holistic health and empowerment coach\n| [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| Split at wedding\n|-\n| Kenny Barnes\n| 27\n| Sales\n| [[California]]\n| Split at wedding\n|-\n| Diamond Jack\n| 28\n| Former [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] dancer\n| [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| Split before the wedding\n|-\n| Carlton Morton\n| 34\n| Social media marketer\n| [[Louisiana]]\n| Split before the wedding\n|-\n| Danielle Drouin\n| 27\n| Yoga instructor\n| [[Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| Split before the wedding{{efn|name=Did not air|This relationship and engagement was not aired in the final cut, but was confirmed by the series creator, Chris Coelen.<ref name=\"other engagements\"/><ref name=\"failed engagements\">{{cite web |last1=Falcone |first1=Dana |title=Love Is Blind Helped 2 More Couples Get Engaged: Why Netflix Didn't Show Their Stories |url=https://people.com/tv/love-is-blind-helped-2-more-couples-get-engaged-why-netflix-didnt-show-their-stories/ |website=people.com |publisher=People |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |language=English |date=February 27, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| Rory Newbrough\n| 28\n| Senior consultant and content creator\n| [[Alpharetta, Georgia]]\n| Split before the wedding{{efn|name=Did not air}}\n|-\n| Lexie Skipper\n| 26\n| Sales manager\n| [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]\n| Split before the wedding{{efn|name=Did not