arch 2]]\n** [[Desi Arnaz]], Cuban-born American actor, bandleader, musician, and television producer; co-founder of [[Desilu Productions]] (d. [[1986]])\n** [[Babiker Awadalla]], 8th [[Prime Minister of Sudan]] (d. [[2019]])\n** [[Laurie Baker]], English architect (d. [[2007]])\n** [[Max Webb]], Polish-American real estate developer and philanthropist (d. [[2018]])\n* [[March 3]] &ndash; [[Sameera Moussa]], Egyptian nuclear scientist (d. [[1952]])\n* [[March 4]] &ndash; [[Clyde McCullough]], American baseball catcher (d. [[1982]])\n* [[March 5]] &ndash; [[Raymond P. Shafer]], Governor of Pennsylvania (d. [[2006]])\n* [[March 6]]\n** [[Samael Aun Weor]], Colombian writer (d. [[1977]])\n** [[Ruth Dayan]], Israeli fashion designer\n** [[Will Eisner]], American cartoonist (d. [[2005]])\n* [[March 9]] &ndash; [[Jack Laver]], Tasmanian cricketer (d. [[2017]])\n* [[March 10]] \n** [[Edith Iglauer]], American writer (d. [[2019]])\n** [[Zbigniew \u015acibor-Rylski]], Polish Brigadier General (d. [[2018]])\n* [[March 11]] &ndash; [[James Megellas]], United States Army officer (d. [[2020]])\n* [[March 12]]\n** [[Giovanni Benedetti]], Italian Catholic prelate (d. [[2017]])\n** [[Leonard Chess]], American record company executive, co-founder of [[Chess Records]] (d. [[1969]])\n** [[Googie Withers]], British actress (d. [[2011]])\n* [[March 16]] &ndash; [[Mehrdad Pahlbod]], Iranian royal and politician (d. [[2018]])\n* [[March 18]] &ndash; [[Mircea Ionescu-Quintus]], Romanian politician (d. [[2017]])\n* [[March 19]] \n** [[Dinu Lipatti]], Romanian pianist (d. [[1950]])\n** [[Peggy Ahern]], American actress (d. [[2012]])\n** [[Sardon Jubir]], Malaysian politician (d. [[1985]])\n* [[March 20]]\n** [[Haddon Donald]], New Zealand Army Lieutenant Colonel and politician (d. [[2018]]) \n** [[Vera Lynn]], English actress, singer \n* [[March 21]] \n** [[Anton Coppola]], American opera conductor, composer (d. [[2020]])\n** [[Yigael Yadin]], Israeli archeologist, politician, and Military Chief of Staff (d. [[1984]])\n* [[March 22]] &ndash; [[Virginia Grey]], American actress (d. [[2004]])\n* [[March 23]] &ndash; [[Kenneth Tobey]], American actor (d. [[2002]])\n* [[March 24]]\n** [[Constantine Andreou]], Brazilian-Greek artist (d. [[2007]])\n** [[John Kendrew]], British molecular biologist, recipient of the [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry]] (d. [[1997]])\n* [[March 26]] &ndash; [[Rufus Thomas]], American singer (d. [[2001]])\n* [[March 27]]\n** [[Takumi Furukawa]], Japanese film director (d. [[2018]])\n** [[Cyrus Vance]], American politician (d. [[2002]])\n* [[March 29]] &ndash; [[Man o' War]], champion thoroughbred racehorse (d. [[1947]])\n\n=== April ===\n[[File:Robert Bloch with His Award.jpg|120px|thumb|[[Robert Bloch]]]]\n[[File:Robert Woodward Nobel.jpg|thumb|120px|[[Robert Burns Woodward]]]]\n[[File:Ella Fitzgerald (Gottlieb 02871).jpg|thumb|120px|[[Ella Fitzgerald]]]]\n[[File:I.M. Pei.JPG|thumb|120px|[[I. M. Pei]]]]\n* [[April 1]] \n** [[Sydney Newman]], Canadian-born television producer (d. [[1997]])\n** [[Leon Janney]], American actor (d. [[1980]])\n* [[April 2]] &ndash; [[Dabbs Greer]], American actor (d. [[2007]])\n* [[April 3]] &ndash; [[Edward Rowny]], American army lieutenant general (d. [[2017]])\n* [[April 5]] &ndash; [[Robert Bloch]], American writer (d. [[1994]])\n* [[April 7]] &ndash; [[R. G. Armstrong]], American actor (d. [[2012]])\n* [[April 8]]\n** [[John Whitney (animator)|John Whitney]], American animator, composer, and pioneer in [[computer animation]] (d. [[1995]])\n** [[Hubertus Ernst]], Dutch Roman Catholic prelate (d. [[2017]])\n* [[April 9]] &ndash; [[Brad Dexter]], American actor (d. [[2002]])\n* [[April 10]] &ndash; [[Robert Burns Woodward]], American chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. [[1979]])\n* [[April 11]] &ndash; [[Morton Sobell]], American spy (d. [[2018]])\n* [[April 12]] &ndash; [[D\u017eemal Bijedi\u0107]], Yugoslav politician (d. [[1977]])\n* [[April 13]]\n** [[Robert O. Anderson]], A