(b. [[1842]])\n* [[November 8]] &ndash; [[Colin Blythe]], English cricketer (b. [[1879]])\n* [[November 11]] &ndash; [[Lili\u02bbuokalani]], last monarch of the [[Kingdom of Hawaii]] (b. [[1838]])\n* [[November 15]] &ndash; [[\u00c9mile Durkheim]], French sociologist (b. [[1858]])\n* [[November 16]] &ndash; [[Adolf Reinach]], German philosopher (killed in action) (b. [[1883]])\n* [[November 17]]\n** [[Neil Primrose (politician)|Neil Primrose]], British Liberal MP (killed in action) (b. [[1882]])\n** [[Auguste Rodin]], French sculptor (b. [[1840]])\n* [[December 8]] &ndash; [[Mendele Mocher Sforim]], Russian Yiddish, Hebrew writer (b. [[1836]])\n* [[December 10]] &ndash; [[Mackenzie Bowell|Sir Mackenzie Bowell]], 5th [[Prime Minister of Canada]] (b. [[1823]])\n* [[December 12]] &ndash; [[Andrew Taylor Still]], American father of osteopathy (b. [[1828]])\n* [[December 17]] &ndash; [[Elizabeth Garrett Anderson]], English physician and suffragette (b. [[1836]])\n* [[December 19]] &ndash; [[Richard Maybery]], British fighter ace (killed in action) (b. [[1895]])\n* [[December 20]] &ndash; [[Eric Campbell (actor)|Eric Campbell]], Scottish actor (accident) (b. [[1879]])\n* [[December 22]]\n** [[Frances Xavier Cabrini]], first American canonized as a saint (b. [[1850]])\n** [[Stanis\u0142aw Tondos]], Polish painter (b. [[1854]])\n* [[December 24]] &ndash; [[Ivan Goremykin]], Russian statesman, former Prime Minister (b. [[1839]])\n* [[December 28]] &ndash; [[Alfred Edwin McKay]], Canadian fighter ace (killed in action) (b. [[1892]])\n\n== Nobel Prizes ==\n[[File:Nobel medal.png|right|100px]]\n* [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Physics]] &ndash; [[Charles Glover Barkla]]\n* [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Chemistry]] &ndash; not awarded\n* [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Medicine]] &ndash; not awarded\n* [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Literature]] &ndash; [[Karl Adolph Gjellerup]], [[Henrik Pontoppidan]]\n* [[Nobel Peace Prize|Peace]] &ndash; [[International Committee of the Red Cross